==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: gooseflesh
<hw>gooseflesh</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A peculiar roughness of the skin
produced by cold or fear, in which the hair follicles become erect and
form bumps on the skin; -- called also <altname>goose skin</altname>,
<altname>goose pimples</altname>, <altname>goose
bumps</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> goose bumps, goose pimples, goose skin.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goosefoot</ent>⟦br⟧
